		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">Charm as Taunt<br clear=all>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Sun, Aug 20th 3:49 PM2000 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=4&mid=96680098213065&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=4&mid=96680098213065&num=2&post=1&replyto=96680098213065"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=96680098213065></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=720"><span id=>KraxusMaclir</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br>4 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=KraxusMaclir&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>A simple tip for the Bards of this world to employ in later levels.&nbsp;&nbsp;At level 27 and then again at Level 39 a Bard can aquire a song that allows us to temporarily charm a mob.<br><br>Heres how it goews.<br><br>When in a group and for whatever reason a mob is fixed on any one target (the warrior for dealing way too much damage or the cleric for healing the warrior who is nearly dead from dealing that damage, for example) and nothing that anyone else can do is taunting the mob off of that person the Bard can, surprisingly, step in and rule.<br><br>Its quite simple and may be againt common thought but all you need to do is successfully charm the mob that will not be taunted by the paladin, ranger etc etc.   Once succesfully charmed that mobs hate list is erased and, for the 15 seconds that the Bard charm lasts, that mob is YOUR pet.  This can allow the cleric to recover and heal or allow the fighter to back out of range or in extreme cases for the druid to pull off an evac.  When the charm breaks the mob is instantly aggroed on you and not the previous player (yeah I know its rough being a bard, but hey we dont just wear plate mail for the looks) and the rest of the group can then proceed with combat as normal and finish the mob.<br><br>I can now say that I have used this tactic more times than I can remember and quite simply put it saves lives.  Be sure, however, that when employing this tactic to keep the group aware of what is going on.  Theres nothing that will annoy a caster more than wasting mana on a mob that is currently bard charmed.<br><br>Thats all there is to it.<br><br>Kraxus Maclir - Roadrunner Extrodinaire<br>Shining Alliance<br>40th Bard<br><br>"Meep Meep"</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >2 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Mon, Aug 21st 1:42 AM2000 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=4&mid=96680098213065&num=2&post=1&replyto=96683653431069"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=96683653431069></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.66]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>I agree with you Kraxus :o)&nbsp;&nbsp;Charm is the "uber" taunt and I use to tell the casters in my group, that once a mob locks on them, they should yell, and I would charm it. But it is necessary to point out, that it takes a few seconds to target the mob (if you fight multiple mobs) and successfully charm it - there are occasionally resists that will delay the charm...  :o(   <br><br>I also like to charm a mob and to share the damage. Often I team with a warrior and when he comes back with a pull, he takes all the damage during the fight and therefore we have more downtime (cause I need more time to heal him). So I usually charm the mob once the warrior has pulled it and take about 1 bub of damage - then the warrior has dealt so much damage that he is going to take the beating from there on. If necessary I will recharm during the fight to take more smacks from the target. Using this technique a lvl 52 warrior and me have been able to kill a LDC without to much sweat (we were both at 2 bubbles of health). <br><br>The time a charm lasts is anywhere from 1 second to about 15 seconds and equipping a lute should reduce resists (for me it does) and also enhances the duration of the charm (sometimes).<br><br>Another use for charm is when you have to make a run for the border&#8230; just hit charm -cause like all bard songs it works even when you walk/run- and probably you will successfully charm your target and have one less beating on you/your group on your way out.<br><br>Sgrobi Lutebasher<br>Bard of 48 strings, E&#8217;ci<br></p></td></td></tr><tr><td col